  <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="shortdesc:1;25:14">A single repository can contain content that must meet different
  editorial standards — for example, a tutorial section and an API reference
  section with distinct metadata requirements. Use separate rule set files and
  specify the correct one at runtime with the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;28:55">--rules</codeph>
  option.</shortdesc>

  <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="conbody:1;31:12">

    <section id="why-multiple" class="- topic/section " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="section:1;33:32">
      <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="title:2;34:14">When to use more than one rule set</title>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="p:1;35:10">A single rule set works well when all content in the repository
      follows the same standards. Use multiple rule sets when:</p>
      <ul class="- topic/ul " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="ul:1;37:11">
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="li:1;38:13"><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="b:1;38:16">Different content types have different metadata requirements.</b>
        For example, tutorial articles must have <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="codeph:2;39:58">ms.topic:
        tutorial</codeph> and a "Prerequisites" section, while API reference
        articles do not.</li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="li:2;42:13"><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="b:2;42:16">Different teams own different subdirectories</b> and maintain
        their own editorial standards independently.</li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="li:3;44:13"><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="b:3;44:16">You are migrating from one standard to another</b> and need to
        run the old rule set against existing content and the new rule set
        against new content simultaneously.</li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="li:4;47:13"><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="b:4;47:16">One rule set is shared across repositories</b> (for example, a
        base style standard) while each repository adds its own
        product-specific rules on top.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="specifying-rules" class="- topic/section " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="section:2;53:36">
      <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="title:3;54:14">Specifying the rule set at runtime</title>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="p:2;55:10">The <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="codeph:3;55:22">--rules</codeph> option accepts any path to a JSON rule
      set file. You can run the validator multiple times against different
      directories using different rule sets:</p>

      <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="codeblock:1;59:39"># Validate tutorials with the tutorial rule set
md-validate validate docs/tutorials/ --rules rules/tutorials.json

# Validate API reference with the reference rule set
md-validate validate docs/reference/ --rules rules/api-reference.json</codeblock>

      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="p:3;65:10">There is no configuration file that automatically selects the rule
      set. The rule set is always specified explicitly on the command line —
      either by the author running the tool locally or by the CI pipeline.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="how-authors-know" class="- topic/section " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="section:3;70:36">
      <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="title:4;71:14">How authors know which rule set applies</title>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="p:4;72:10">Document the rule set path in your repository's contributing guide.
      Common conventions:</p>
      <ul class="- topic/ul " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="ul:2;74:11">
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="li:5;75:13"><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="b:5;75:16">By directory</b> — <filepath class="+ topic/ph sw-d/filepath " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="filepath:1;75:45">docs/tutorials/</filepath> uses
        <filepath class="+ topic/ph sw-d/filepath " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="filepath:2;76:19">rules/tutorials.json</filepath>, etc.</li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="li:6;77:13"><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="b:6;77:16">By front-matter field</b> — <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="codeph:4;77:52">ms.topic</codeph> value maps
        to a rule set.</li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="li:7;79:13"><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="b:7;79:16">Script wrapper</b> — a <filepath class="+ topic/ph sw-d/filepath " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="filepath:3;79:49">validate.sh</filepath> script
        picks the rule set automatically based on file path.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="p:5;82:10">Whatever convention you use, the local path must match the one CI uses.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="ci-matrix" class="- topic/section " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="section:4;85:29">
      <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="title:5;86:14">CI configuration for multiple rule sets</title>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="p:6;87:10">When you have two or more rule sets, each one should run as a
      separate CI job so that failures in one area do not suppress failures
      in another. Use a GitHub Actions matrix strategy to avoid duplicating
      the job definition:</p>

      <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="codeblock:2;92:39">jobs:
  validate:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    strategy:
      matrix:
        include:
          - docs-dir: docs/tutorials/
            rules-file: rules/tutorials.json
            artifact-name: reports-tutorials
          - docs-dir: docs/reference/
            rules-file: rules/api-reference.json
            artifact-name: reports-reference

    steps:
      - name: Check out repository
        uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Set up Python
        uses: actions/setup-python@v5
        with:
          python-version: '3.12'

      - name: Cache NLTK data
        uses: actions/cache@v4
        with:
          path: ~/nltk_data
          key: nltk-punkt-tagger

      - name: Install markdown-validator
        run: pip install markdown-validator

      - name: Download NLTK language data
        run: python -m nltk.downloader punkt_tab averaged_perceptron_tagger_eng

      - name: Validate documentation
        run: |
          md-validate validate ${{ matrix.docs-dir }} \
            --rules ${{ matrix.rules-file }} \
            --format json \
            --output reports/

      - name: Upload validation reports
        if: always()
        uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
        with:
          name: ${{ matrix.artifact-name }}
          path: reports/</codeblock>

      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="p:7;140:10">Each matrix entry produces a separate check on the pull request. A
      failure in tutorials does not prevent the reference check from running
      and reporting its own result.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="local-ci-mismatch" class="- topic/section " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="section:5;145:37">
      <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="title:6;146:14">Preventing local vs. CI rule mismatch</title>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="p:8;147:10">The most common multi-ruleset problem: an author validates with the
      wrong rule set locally and sees different failures in CI.</p>
      <ul class="- topic/ul " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="ul:3;149:11">
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="li:8;150:13"><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="b:8;150:16">Commit all rule set files.</b> Never use local copies that
        diverge from source control.</li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="li:9;152:13"><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="b:9;152:16">Document the exact command</b> in the contributing guide,
        including the full <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="codeph:5;153:36">--rules</codeph> path.</li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="li:10;154:13"><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="b:10;154:16">Verify the CI <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="codeph:6;154:38">--rules</codeph> value</b> in
        <filepath class="+ topic/ph sw-d/filepath " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="filepath:4;155:19">.github/workflows/validate-docs.yml</filepath> matches
        what authors use locally.</li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="li:11;157:13"><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="b:11;157:16">Pin shared rule sets</b> if they are shared via a package or
        submodule — uncoordinated updates cause hard-to-trace CI failures.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="p:9;160:10">If local and CI results differ, check that <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="codeph:7;160:61">--rules</codeph>
      is identical in both. See also
      <xref href="../../troubleshooting/ts_ci-fails.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_multiple-rulesets.dita" xtrc="xref:1;162:59" type="troubleshooting"><?ditaot usertext?>Resolve a validation failure in CI<?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">When the validation step in your CI pipeline fails, your pull request   is blocked. This topic shows you how to find the failure report, reproduce the   failure locally, and resolve the specific issue.</desc></xref>.</p>
    </section>

  </conbody>
</concept>